{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:joshua.19",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "joshua",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Joshua 19 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:1",
      "text": "And the second lot came out for the children of Symeon; and their inheritance was in the midst of the lots of the children of Juda.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:2",
      "text": "And their lot was Beersabee, and Samaa, and Caladam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:3",
      "text": "and Arsola, and Bola, and Jason,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:4",
      "text": "and Erthula, and Bula, and Herma,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:5",
      "text": "and Sikelac, and Baethmachereb, and Sarsusin,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:6",
      "text": "and Batharoth, and their fields, thirteen cities, and their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:7",
      "text": "Eremmon, and Thalcha, and Jether, and Asan; four cities and their villages,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:8",
      "text": "round about their cities as far as Balec as men go to Bameth southward: this is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Symeon according to their families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:9",
      "text": "The inheritance of the tribe of the children of Symeon was a part of the lot of Juda, for the portion of the children of Juda was greater than theirs; and the children of Symeon inherited in the midst of their lot.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:10",
      "text": "And the third lot came out to Zabulon according to their families: the bounds of their inheritance shall be—Esedekgola shall be their border,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:11",
      "text": "the sea and Magelda, and it shall reach to Baetharaba in the valley, which is opposite Jekman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:12",
      "text": "And the border returned from Sedduc in a contrary direction eastward from Baethsamys, to the borders of Chaselothaith, and shall pass on to Dabiroth, and shall proceed upward to Phangai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:13",
      "text": "And thence it shall come round in the opposite direction eastward to Gebere to the city of Catasem, and shall go on to Remmonaa Matharaoza.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:14",
      "text": "And the borders shall come round northward to Amoth, and their going out shall be at Gaephael,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:15",
      "text": "and Catanath, and Nabaal, and Symoon, and Jericho, and Baethman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:16",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Zabulon according to their families, these cities and their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:17",
      "text": "And the fourth lot came out to Issachar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:18",
      "text": "And their borders were Jazel, and Chasaloth, and Sunam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:19",
      "text": "and Agin, and Siona, and Reeroth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:20",
      "text": "and Anachereth, and Dabiron, and Kison, and Rebes,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:21",
      "text": "and Remmas, and Jeon, and Tomman, and Æmarec, and Bersaphes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:22",
      "text": "And the boundaries shall border upon Gaethbor, and upon Salim westward, and Baethsamys; and the extremity of his bounds shall be Jordan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:23",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Issachar according to their families, the cities and their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:24",
      "text": "And the fifth lot came out to Aser according to their families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:25",
      "text": "And their borders were Exeleketh, and Aleph, and Baethok, and Keaph,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:26",
      "text": "and Elimelech, and Amiel, and Maasa, and the lot will border on Carmel westward, and on Sion, and Labanath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:27",
      "text": "And it will return westward from Baethegeneth, and will join Zabulon and Ekgai, and Phthaeel northwards, and the borders will come to Saphthaebaethme, and Inael, and will go on to Chobamasomel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:28",
      "text": "and Elbon, and Raab, and Ememaon, and Canthan to great Sidon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:29",
      "text": "And the borders shall turn back to Rama, and to the fountain of Masphassat, and the Tyrians; and the borders shall return to Jasiph, and their going forth shall be the sea, and Apoleb, and Echozob,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:30",
      "text": "and Archob, and Aphec, and Raau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:31",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Aser according to their families, the cities and their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:32",
      "text": "And the sixth lot came out to Nephthali.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:33",
      "text": "And their borders were Moolam, and Mola, and Besemiin, and Arme, and Naboc, and Jephthamai, as far as Dodam; and their goings out were Jordan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:34",
      "text": "And the coasts will return westward by Athabor, and will go out thence to Jacana, and will border on Zabulon southward, and Aser will join it westward, and Jordan eastward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:35",
      "text": "And the walled cities of the Tyrians, Tyre, and Omathadaketh, and Kenereth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.36",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:36",
      "text": "and Armaith, and Areal, and Asor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.37",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:37",
      "text": "and Cades, and Assari, and the well of Asor;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.38",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:38",
      "text": "and Keroe, and Megalaarim, and Baetthame, and Thessamys.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.39",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:39",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Nephthali.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.40",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:40",
      "text": "And the seventh lot came out to Dan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.41",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:41",
      "text": "And their borders were Sarath, and Asa, and the cities of Sammaus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.42",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:42",
      "text": "and Salamin, and Ammon, and Silatha,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.43",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:43",
      "text": "and Elon, and Thamnatha, and Accaron;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.44",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:44",
      "text": "and Alcatha, and Begethon, and Gebeelan,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.45",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:45",
      "text": "and Azor, and Banaebacat, and Gethremmon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.46",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:46",
      "text": "And westward of Hieracon the border was near to Joppa.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.47",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:47",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Dan, according to their families, these are their cities and their villages: and the children of Dan did not drive out the Amorite who afflicted them in the mountain; and the Amorite would not suffer them to come down into the valley, but they forcibly took from them the border of their portion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.48",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:48",
      "text": "And the sons of Dan went and fought against Lachis, and took it, and smote it with the edge of the sword; and they dwelt in it, and called the name of it Lasendan: and the Amorite continued to dwell in Edom and in Salamin: and the hand of Ephraim prevailed against them, and they became tributaries to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.49",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:49",
      "text": "And they proceeded to take possession of the land according to their borders, and the children of Israel gave an inheritance to Joshua the son of Naue among them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.50",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:50",
      "text": "by the command of God, and they gave him the city which he asked for, Thamnasarach, which is in the mount of Ephraim; and he built the city, and dwelt in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:joshua.19.51",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:51",
      "text": "These are the divisions which Eleazar the priest divided by lot, and Joshua the son of Naue, and the heads of families among the tribes of Israel, according to the lots, in Selo before the Lord by the doors of the tabernacle of testimony, and they went to take possession of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
